<td width="450" ><font face="Arial,Helvetica" size="2"><b>Using the "/who" Command</b></td><tr>
<td width="450" ><font face="Arial,Helvetica" size="2">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The /who command is very useful. You can gather a lot of information with it.

1. You can use it to check if someone is online by typing "/who all (name)" replacing (name) with the name of the person. 2. You can use it to find out the race, class, level, of another person. 3. Use it to find out if any of the persons on your friends list are online by typing: "/who all friends". 4. You can find others who are close to your level by typing: "/who (level)" replacing (level) with a level close to yours. -Pyro....feel the heat! </td>
</table>
</center><br>
