<td width="450" ><font face="Arial,Helvetica" size="2"><b>FORAGING SKILL</b></td><tr>
<td width="450" ><font face="Arial,Helvetica" size="2">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Druids and Rangers harken to my words, by accident I discovered that you may practice your skill of Foraging while sitting or even meditating. You may well scoff at this information  but it is true. While you will get a message that you must be standing to forage iit still counts as a practice. I discovered this by accidently hitting my hot key for the skill while medding and saw the announcement that my skill had risen. I have since had Forage raise twice more while medding. so no more standing unless you REALLY need the food to up this skill.---Sullivyn Briarthorn, Druid </td>
</table>
