<td width="450" ><font face="Arial,Helvetica" size="2"><b>/loc hot key..</b></td><tr>
<td width="450" ><font face="Arial,Helvetica" size="2">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;if you go into the area where you have the buttons for afk and others, you can right click on one of these useless buttons, and rename it to...loc and then make the command /loc..then take this button and but it in your hot keys.  very helpful when you are tring to find something, and you know it's loc (like, say, your corpse) just as you run click this /loc command over and over untill the numbers are going in the right direction and you will find what you are looking for easier then you ever thought you would, plus, if you are about to die, it's easier to click the button on your hotkeys then it is to type /loc..  

(this idea also works great for /corpse--and others--where you have to get your corpse out of somewhere dangerious, just run by it (invis helps) and start clicking the 'corpse' button, while you run to safty.  When you get somewhere safe stop and you will have quickly successfully draged your corpse accross the land, and not had to stop to loot it, plus, if you have invis, you are still invis, where if you looted it you would have lost the invis)

just my 2cp 

:)

</td>
