<!-- 152.163.201.197 -->

<center>
<table border="2" width="450" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
<td width="450" ><font face="Arial,Helvetica" size="2"><b>Casters intentional train</b></td><tr>
<td width="450" ><font face="Arial,Helvetica" size="2">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Tired of idiots that constantly make trains in BlackBurrow and then run right back after they've safely zoned? Make the mother of all trains this way once you know that idiot is back down for round whatever. On top of BB, , right out of the Qeynos hills zone, you'll see a pit that overlooks a lake. You'll also see a bridge leading to a doorway. At that doorway you'll usually see a sitting gnoll guardsman and if you creep up to the edge of the pit (careful not to go too far), you'll be able to cast on that gnoll. Use a spell such as siphon strength, and that gnoll will run off, gather his friends and head for the top creating a train of as many as 15 gnolls. If you give it a few seconds, and then zone out before they get to the top , those gnolls will be running around BB until they find someone else who's killing any old gnoll...one hopes it'll be your friend the conductor of the Gnoll express. Be nice and warn everybody that you'll be exterminating train pests before you do this. This technique is also good for a group of lvl 9 - 15 as the mob coming up top will provide tons of exp if you choose to remain inside after casting...just be aware that they'll be gunning for YOU, the caster, first.</td>
</table>
</center><br>
<!-- 216.200.49.81 -->

<center>
<table border="2" width="450" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
<td width="450" ><font face="Arial,Helvetica" size="2"><b>Saving platinum </b></td><tr>
<td width="450" ><font face="Arial,Helvetica" size="2">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Every point of charisma counts when buying from and selling to merchants. For about 7-8 platinum you can buy a silk evening shirt from a female vendor near the Qeynos docks that has a +5 cha stat. It is very light and will help you save literally 100's of platinum throughout your characters carreer.

Also the best +dex jewelry for the money is star ruby rings which cost an enchanter around 88 platinum to make, plus failure rates of course. They are +7 dex and +5 cha. This will also not only help you save money but the +14 dex is the best deal out there for melee classes and cost much less than two fire emerald rings until you can upgrade.</td>
</table>
</center><br>
