<center>
<table border="2" width="450" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
<td width="450" ><font face="Arial,Helvetica" size="2"><b>Keeping a monk's weight low</b></td><tr>
<td width="450" ><font face="Arial,Helvetica" size="2">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;I have found that carrying spits (used to make food) are the best containers for monks.  They hold 6 items and only weigh 0.2 each.  I have yet to find anything they can't hold (even bear pelts).      -Krystel</td>
</table>
</center><br>
